    <sectiondef kind="enum">
      <memberdef kind="enum" id="HipdnnBackendPluginLoadingMode_8h_1a51d3b5d4dd140eaf46fa19908ceb302a" prot="public" static="no" strong="no">
        <type></type>
        <name>hipdnnPluginLoadingMode_ext_t</name>
        <enumvalue id="HipdnnBackendPluginLoadingMode_8h_1a51d3b5d4dd140eaf46fa19908ceb302aa7f7d0c2ecde2bb9abc14d4a56725d7a2" prot="public">
          <name>HIPDNN_PLUGIN_LOADING_ADDITIVE</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Additive loading mode (default) </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Loads all user-specified plugins in addition to the default plugins. This is useful when you want to extend hipDNN with custom plugins while retaining access to the built-in implementations. </para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="HipdnnBackendPluginLoadingMode_8h_1a51d3b5d4dd140eaf46fa19908ceb302aa9610835db63d2e5a242c13f5f403f7e2" prot="public">
          <name>HIPDNN_PLUGIN_LOADING_ABSOLUTE</name>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Absolute loading mode. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Loads only the user-specified plugin from the most recent registration call, ignoring all default plugins. This is useful when you want complete control over which plugins are active. </para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Specifies the plugin loading mode for hipDNN (extension API) </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This enumeration defines how plugins are loaded into hipDNN. The loading mode affects which plugins are available for engine discovery and execution.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para>hipdnnRegisterEnginePlugin_ext() </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
